Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{0.5%tsp} on to boil for the pasta.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}(halved and thinly sliced). Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @courgette{1}. Use a #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the courgette, stopping at the spongy centre.

Zest and halve the @lemon{0.5}(zested and halved).

Once boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

When ready, reserve some of the pasta water (see pantry for amount), then drain in a #colander{}.

Pop the pasta back into the saucepan, drizzle with oil and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add the courgette ribbons and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Add the @baby spinach{100%g} a handful at a time and cook until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Transfer everything to a large #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Put your (now empty) frying pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced british chicken breast{1%pack} and shallot and cook, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @reserved pasta water{100%ml}, then simmer until reduced by half, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Mix in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and heat through until piping hot, then season with @pepper{}.

Stir three quarters of the @grated hard italian style cheese{40%g} through your creamy sauce.

Add the cooked pasta and half the cooked green veg and stir well to combine. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Add a pinch of lemon zest and a squeeze of lemon juice. Taste and add more lemon juice, salt and pepper if needed.

Share the creamy chicken pasta between your bowls and top with the remaining cooked green veg.

Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining hard Italian style cheese.

Enjoy!